# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ShinobiX environment variables (template — no real values, safe to commit).
#
# Local dev:  copy to `.env` (loaded by app.js via dotenv).
# Railway / Render / Fly / VPS:  set these in the platform's dashboard/secrets,
#                                NOT in a committed file.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Database — pick ONE path ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Recommended off-Vercel (Railway/VPS/cPanel): direct Postgres pool.
# When DATABASE_URL is set and the app is NOT running on Vercel, the server uses
# the pg connection pool — the same, battle-tested code path as cPanel
# (api/_storage.ts:712). Paste your Supabase "Connection string" here; the app
# auto-strips sslmode/pgbouncer params, so the pooler URI works as-is.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:5432/postgres

# Alternative: Supabase REST API path. Used ONLY if DATABASE_URL is unset.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ── Auth / secrets (required) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Long random string. Enables fast stateless session tokens; WITHOUT it every
# authenticated request falls back to a ~100ms scrypt verify. Rotating this value
# invalidates all existing sessions (logs everyone out).
SESSION_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-string

# Admin panel password.
ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me

# Content-moderation admin password (bloodline/item review, etc.).
ADMIN_CONTENT_PASSWORD=change-me

# ── Recommended ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The daily save-snapshot backup now runs IN-PROCESS on the always-on server
# (03:00 UTC — see api/cron/_scheduler.ts), so you do NOT need an external cron.
# CRON_SECRET only still guards the manual HTTP trigger GET /api/cron/snapshot-saves
# (admins can also trigger it with the admin password); set it if you want a
# Bearer-token way to hit that endpoint.
CRON_SECRET=change-me

# Secret guarding POST /restart (graceful process restart endpoint).
RESTART_TOKEN=change-me

# ── Optional ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed if the in-game AI image generation endpoint is used.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ── Realtime / background-job toggles (optional) ─────────────────────────────
# Disable the Socket.IO presence layer (clients fall back to the HTTP heartbeat).
# Leave unset on the primary instance so realtime is ON.
# DISABLE_REALTIME=1
#
# Skip the in-process daily save-snapshot on THIS instance. Set on any SECONDARY
# instance (e.g. cPanel) so only the primary (Railway) runs the nightly backup —
# the 20h dedup window makes a double run harmless, this just avoids a redundant
# keyspace scan. Leave unset on the primary so backups run.
# DISABLE_SNAPSHOT_CRON=1
#
# Client (build-time) — point the game Socket.IO connection at a remote backend
# for cross-origin dev. Unset = same-origin (correct in production).
# VITE_REALTIME_URL=https://your-backend.example.com

# ── Postgres connection tuning (pg pool path only) ───────────────────────────
# Pool size PER process. Default 5 (fine for cPanel's many worker processes).
# A single always-on Railway/VPS instance serving all heartbeat writes wants
# more — set ~15 on Railway.
# PG_POOL_MAX=15
#
# SSL. Default = TLS on (required by Supabase and Railway's PUBLIC proxy URL).
# Set to "disable" ONLY when connecting over Railway's PRIVATE network
# (host ends in .railway.internal), which serves plaintext on an isolated
# per-project overlay and rejects an SSL handshake. Do NOT disable SSL on any
# public/internet connection string.
# PG_SSL=disable

# ── Storage mode: where save:* / shared:images* keys live (PICK ONE) ─────────
# The server runs in one of two storage topologies. Be explicit about which:
#
#  A) Supabase-only (simplest). Every key — including player saves — lives on the
#     base Postgres/Supabase store. Leave DISK_KV_DIR and KV_PROXY_* unset.
#
#  B) cPanel disk overlay (PRODUCTION). save: / save-snapshot: / shared:images /
#     shared:imgfields keys route to the free cPanel disk (unlimited bandwidth —
#     keeps heavy save/image blobs off metered Railway egress AND off Supabase).
#     Railway reaches it over HTTP via the KV proxy; cPanel reads the disk directly.
#         # On Railway (remote → cPanel proxy):
#         KV_PROXY_URL=https://theravensark.com/api/kv
#         KV_PROXY_TOKEN=<shared secret, identical to the cPanel box's KV token>
#         # On the cPanel box itself (direct disk; NOT on Railway):
#         DISK_KV_DIR=/home/USER/kv-storage
#
#  ‼ CRITICAL fail-closed guard. On ANY instance that serves /api/save/* from the
#  overlay (mode B), set REQUIRE_DISK_OVERLAY=1. The server then REFUSES TO BOOT
#  if the overlay env is missing instead of silently falling back to the (empty)
#  base store — that fallback makes every player look logged-out/wiped and writes
#  new progress to the wrong store. The /health?deep=1 probe reports `saveStore`
#  ("disk" / "remote-proxy" / "base-store") so you can confirm routing after a
#  deploy; "base-store" on a save-serving host means saves are MISROUTED. Leave
#  REQUIRE_DISK_OVERLAY unset only on a deliberate mode-A (Supabase-only) instance.
# REQUIRE_DISK_OVERLAY=1
#
# SUPABASE_HARDCODED_IP — cPanel only. The CageFS DNS bypass IP for *.supabase.co
#   (a Cloudflare anycast IP that can rotate). Override here if Supabase rotates it,
#   so it's a config change + restart, not a code edit. Falls back to a known-good IP.
# SUPABASE_HARDCODED_IP=172.64.149.246

# ── Do NOT set on Railway / containers ───────────────────────────────────────
#   PORT        — injected by the platform; the server reads it automatically.
#   STATIC_DIR  — default already resolves to shinobij.client/dist in the image.
#   DISK_KV_DIR — local-file overlay; cPanel-only. Containers have an EPHEMERAL
#                 filesystem, so on Railway use the KV_PROXY_* path (mode B above)
#                 to reach the cPanel disk, never DISK_KV_DIR.
#   FORCE_PG_KV — set to 1 only to force the pg path when SUPABASE_URL is also set.
